text: Camellia sasanqua (often called the sasanqua camellia) is a species of plant in the genus Camellia. It is native to China and Japan. It can be found growing at a height of 900 meters. It grows up to 5 meters tall and is related to the tea plant, Camellia sinensis. == References == Category:Camellia
title: Camellia sasanqua
